<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 11 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTO-1X707LL/DLL/MLL AND RTO-1X709MLL MODELS - INSTALL -
        COUNTERSHAFT BEARINGS (1X707 MODELS)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="5">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT BEARINGS (1X707 MODELS)</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the countershaft to the rear and insert the countershaft support tool to center the
                shaft in the rear case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020l5">Figure 215</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020l5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020l5" filename="../figg13/G13020L5.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 215. Center The Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a flanged-end bearing driver and maul to completely seat the front bearing in the case
                bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020l6">Figure 216</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020l6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020l6" filename="../figg13/G13020L6.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 216. Seat The Front Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the front bearing retaining snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020l7">Figure 217</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020l7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020l7" filename="../figg13/G13020L7.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 217. Front Bearing Retainer Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the countershaft support tool from the rear.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With the larger I.D. lead chamfer to the shaft front, use a flanged-end bearing driver and
                install the rear bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020l8">Figure 218</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020l8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020l8" filename="../figg13/G13020L8.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 218. Install Rear Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the rear snap ring in the countershaft rear groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13020l9">Figure 219</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13020l9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13020l9" filename="../figg13/G13020L9.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 219. Install Rear Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
